For customize firewall requirement,
We insert a firewall script in /etc/config/firewall,
this script go through all executable file in "/usr/share/fw3/firewall.d".

config include
  option enabled '1'
  option path '/usr/share/fw3/customized_fw3.sh'
  option type 'script'
  option family 'any'
  option reload '1'

You can change script name to adjust execute order.
For examples:
  s03_xxx --> 's' is normal firewall script.
  p01_xxx --> 'p' is preconfig script, it means this script have higher priority than all normal scripts.
